  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The <span>Residence Ambiez are self catered apartments but can also be booked on bed &amp; breakfast or half board</span></p>
<p><span>Each apartment has a well equipped kitchenette, so you can cook tasty meals from the comfort of your own apartment. Microwaves can be rented for a local fee</span></p>
<p><span>For guests on B&amp;B, breakfast includes a hearty sweet and savoury buffet served until 10am, often including local cheeses, dried meats, cakes and pastries, breads and eggs</span></p>
<p><span>If you have opted into half board, you can enjoy a three course meal, which often includes dishes from the Trentino region</span></p>
<p><span>Meals are taken at the onsite Lares Restaurant</span></p>
<p><span>The Lares Restaurant also has a take-away service available (pay locally)</span></p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>The comfortable apartments at the Residence Ambiez are a great choice for friends and families looking for self catered accommodation in <a data-udi="umb://document/ea59b48ae29b417b81f9c9850d58d038" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ea59b48ae29b417b81f9c9850d58d038}" title="Madonna Di Campiglio" data-anchor="#">Madonna di Campiglio.</a> The residence has some great facilities including a bar, restaurant and wellness area.</span></p>
<h2>Panoramic pool views</h2>
<p>After a day of exploring the Campiglio Ski Area, there is nowhere better to relax than the pool and wellness area.</p>
<p>Guests have free entry to the heated indoor swimming pool, it is the perfect spot to take in the wonderful mountain views. Onsite booking is required for pool access. </p>
<p>After a dip in the pool, adults can head to the Spa Alpes and relax in the Bio or Finnish sauna, unwind in the steam bath or take a relaxing shower in the chromotherapy showers, before heading to the relaxation area with a cup of herbal tea.</p>
<p>The Spa Alpes wellness area is open daily for adults only, there is a small fee per visit, payable locally.</p>
<h2>Eat in or dine out</h2>
<p>These apartments have everything you need for a self-catered stay in the mountains. Each of the apartments has a fully equipped kitchenette with cookware, a ceramic hob, and tea and coffee making facilities - so you can whip up tasty meals from the comfort of your apartment.</p>
<p>If you want to take the fuss out of meals times, you can upgrade to bed and breakfast or half board. Breakfast includes a varied sweet and savoury buffet, often including freshly baked bread, traditional tarts and cakes, pastries, cold cuts, cheese and coffee.</p>
<p>Evening meals include a three course meal with a menu inspired by the Trentino region, this often includes local meats, <span>canederli, polenta and apple strudel.</span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
